Look at MR. MOONEY go! Mr. Mooney is available for adoption here at Cat Love Rescue. He's playful and and is starting to learn how to use the cat wheel. This boy loves water! He is always intrigued with faucets, showers and anything that water comes out of. What a silly boy. He's an overall great cat that would do great in any loving home. He does well with other cats and seems to get along well with dogs. Please contact us for more information and how you can set up a meet and greet in Chino Hills, CA. Mr. Mooney would LOVE to meet you! -- All of our rescue kittens are in foster homes, spayed/neutered, fully vaccinated, tested for FeLV & FIV, dewormed, treated for flea prevention, and fitted with a microchip.

Meet the ever so handsome and charming Smokey! This boy’s happy grin is sure to whisk all your troubles away! He’s not only friendly and connects easily, he loves to show his perfect ‘Sit’ and ‘Shake’! Anything for some head scratches and treats! 😉
Smokey came into the shelter on November 25, 2017 as an Owner Surrender for “Escapes”. It appears they had him his whole life; they reported that Smokey is friendly with children and company. At 9 years old, this lovable guy shouldn’t be sitting in a shelter. Help us to find him a forever home that can keep him safe and secure! Please share, or come meet Smokey today!

Ex-HKDR Sarah @sarahtheloos has waited for a home for 6 years before she became her family’s “spoiled youngest daughter”. Thank you adopters for changing the life of a HKDR long-termer!
.
📝“It’s never too late to fall in love❣️
I am a proud rescued dog. Thank you #hongkongdogrescue staffs, volunteers, my fans and my humoons. You didn’t care how I looked or that I wasn’t a breed. You showed me I am not disposable and that I am loved. You brought back the sparkle in my eyes and the shine of my coat. You restored my spirit so my tail can wag again. You took a chance on me to see what I become. You gave me a place to call home and family to call my own🏡👨‍👩‍👧🐶🐾🐾
In the end, it’s not the years in life that counts, it’s the life in your years”▶️✨💫
.
.
